window.PHP_DOCS_SEARCH_INDEX = [{"title":"Theming","text":" Theming LiteDocs uses Twig as a templating engine. You can easily customize the look and feel. Creating a Theme Create a folder in themes\/ (e.g., themes\/my-theme). Create a base.html.twig file inside. Create an assets\/ folder for your CSS and JS. Available Variables In your Twig templates, you have access to: content: The HTML content of the page. nav: The navigation tree. page_title: The current page title. config: The full configuration array. trans: Translations (based on current language). Overriding Translations You can override any text by creating a translations\/en.yaml file at the root of your project: core: ui: navigation: &quot;Main Menu&quot; ...","url":"en\/advanced\/theming.html"},{"title":"Configuration","text":" Configuration LiteDocs uses a single YAML file named litedocs.yml at the root of your project. Basic Structure Here is a complete example of a configuration file: site_name: &quot;My Documentation&quot; site_url: &quot;https:\/\/example.com&quot; # Directories docs_dir: &quot;docs&quot; site_dir: &quot;site&quot; # Branding logo: &quot;assets\/logo.png&quot; favicon: &quot;assets\/favicon.ico&quot; # Theme theme: name: lite # Imports (Recommended for large projects) nav: &quot;config\/nav.yml&quot; plugins: &quot;config\/plugins.yml&quot; Navigation Configuration You can separate your navigation logic into config\/nav.yml: en: - Home: index.md - Guide: - Setup: guide\/installation.md ...","url":"en\/guide\/configuration.html"},{"title":"Installation","text":" Installation Requirements Before using LiteDocs, ensure your environment meets these requirements: PHP: 8.4 or higher Composer: installed globally (optional if using PHAR) Extensions: php-xml, php-mbstring Option 1: Using the PHAR (Recommended) You can download the standalone executable directly. This is the easiest way to get started. # Download the latest release wget https:\/\/github.com\/ezar101\/litedocs\/releases\/latest\/download\/litedocs.phar # Make it executable chmod +x litedocs.phar # Move to bin (optional) sudo mv litedocs.phar \/usr\/local\/bin\/litedocs Option 2: Using Composer You can also install it as a global dependency: composer global require ezar101\/litedocs Development Workflow When writing documentation, you don't want to run the build command manually every time. Use the watch command to watch for file changes in your docs and themes directories: litedocs watch Live Preview Since LiteDocs is a static site generator, it doesn't include a web server. To preview your site lo...","url":"en\/guide\/installation.html"},{"title":"Plugins System","text":" Plugins System LiteDocs comes with a robust plugin system based on Symfony EventDispatcher. Built-in Plugins We include several powerful plugins out of the box: | Plugin Name | Description | | :--- | :--- | | SearchPlugin | Adds a client-side search engine (JS). | | ReadingTimePlugin | Displays estimated reading time. | | TableOfContentsPlugin | Generates a table of contents on the right side. | | SyntaxHighlightPlugin | Adds colors to your code blocks using Highlight.js. | | SitemapPlugin | Add sitemap.xml for the SEO. | Activation To activate a plugin, add it to your config\/plugins.yml file: LiteDocs\\Plugin\\ReadingTimePlugin: ~ LiteDocs\\Plugin\\SyntaxHighlightPlugin: custom_script: &quot;my-custom-js.js&quot; ...","url":"en\/guide\/plugins.html"},{"title":"Welcome to LiteDocs","text":" Welcome to LiteDocs LiteDocs is a lightweight, modern static site generator written in PHP. It is designed to be fast, extensible, and easy to use for technical documentation. Why LiteDocs? ‚ö° Fast: Generates static HTML files in seconds. üîå Extensible: Plugin system to add features easily. üé® Theming: Modern default theme (Sylius\/GitBook style). üåç Multilingual: Native support for multiple languages. üîç Search: Built-in client-side search engine. Quick Start Run the following command to build your documentation: php bin\/litedocs build Quick Example Here is how you initialize the kernel in PHP: use LiteDocs\\Core\\Kernel; $kernel = new Kernel(__DIR__); $kernel-&gt;boot(); $kernel-&gt;build(); &lt;div data-search-ignore style=&quot;background: #e0f7fa; color: #006064; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; margin-top: 20px;&quot;&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Tip:&lt;\/strong&gt; This block uses the &lt;code&gt;data-search-ignore&lt;\/code&gt; attribute. It will be visible to the user but ignored...","url":"en\/index.html"},{"title":"Th√®mes","text":" Th√®mes LiteDocs utilise Twig comme moteur de template. Vous pouvez facilement personnaliser l'apparence. Cr√©er un Th√®me Cr√©ez un dossier dans themes\/ (ex: themes\/mon-theme). Cr√©ez un fichier base.html.twig √† l'int√©rieur. Cr√©ez un dossier assets\/ pour vos CSS et JS. Variables Disponibles Dans vos templates Twig, vous avez acc√®s √† : content : Le contenu HTML de la page. nav : L'arbre de navigation. page_title : Le titre de la page courante. config : Le tableau complet de configuration. trans : Les traductions (bas√©es sur la langue actuelle). Surcharger les Traductions Vous pouvez surcharger n'importe quel texte en cr√©ant un fichier translations\/fr.yaml √† la racine de votre projet : core: ui: navigation: &quot;Menu Principal&quot; ...","url":"fr\/advanced\/theming.html"},{"title":"Configuration","text":" Configuration LiteDocs utilise un seul fichier YAML nomm√© litedocs.yml √† la racine de votre projet. Structure de Base Voici un exemple complet de fichier de configuration : site_name: &quot;Ma Documentation&quot; site_url: &quot;https:\/\/exemple.com&quot; # Dossiers docs_dir: &quot;docs&quot; site_dir: &quot;site&quot; # Branding logo: &quot;assets\/logo.png&quot; favicon: &quot;assets\/favicon.ico&quot; # Th√®me theme: name: lite # Imports (Recommand√© pour les gros projets) nav: &quot;config\/nav.yml&quot; plugins: &quot;config\/plugins.yml&quot; Configuration de la Navigation Vous pouvez s√©parer votre logique de navigation dans config\/nav.yml: fr: - Accueil: index.md - Guide: - Installation: guide\/installation.md ...","url":"fr\/guide\/configuration.html"},{"title":"Installation","text":" Installation Pr√©requis Avant d'utiliser LiteDocs, assurez-vous que votre environnement respecte ces crit√®res : PHP : 8.4 ou sup√©rieur Composer : install√© globalement (optionnel si PHAR) Extensions : php-xml, php-mbstring Option 1 : Via PHAR (Recommand√©) Vous pouvez t√©l√©charger l'ex√©cutable autonome directement. C'est la m√©thode la plus simple. # T√©l√©charger la derni√®re version wget https:\/\/github.com\/ezar101\/litedocs\/releases\/latest\/download\/litedocs.phar # Rendre ex√©cutable chmod +x litedocs.phar # D√©placer dans bin (optionnel) sudo mv litedocs.phar \/usr\/local\/bin\/litedocs Option 2 : Via Composer Vous pouvez aussi l'installer comme d√©pendance globale : composer global require ezar101\/litedocs Flux de D√©veloppement Lorsque vous r√©digez de la documentation, vous ne voulez pas lancer la commande de build manuellement √† chaque fois. Utilisez la commande watch pour surveiller les modifications dans vos dossiers docs et themes : litedocs watch Pr√©visualisation en direct ...","url":"fr\/guide\/installation.html"},{"title":"Syst√®me de Plugins","text":" Syst√®me de Plugins LiteDocs est livr√© avec un syst√®me de plugins robuste bas√© sur Symfony EventDispatcher. Plugins Int√©gr√©s Nous incluons plusieurs plugins puissants par d√©faut : | Nom du Plugin | Description | | :--- | :--- | | SearchPlugin | Ajoute un moteur de recherche c√¥t√© client (JS). | | ReadingTimePlugin | Affiche le temps de lecture estim√©. | | TableOfContentsPlugin | G√©n√®re une table des mati√®res sur le c√¥t√© droit. | | SyntaxHighlightPlugin | Ajoute des couleurs √† vos blocs de code via Highlight.js. | | SitemapPlugin | Ajoute sitemap.xml pour le SEO. | Activation Pour activer un plugin, ajoutez-le √† votre fichier config\/plugins.yml : LiteDocs\\Plugin\\ReadingTimePlugin: ~ LiteDocs\\Plugin\\SyntaxHighlightPlugin: custom_script: &quot;mon-script-js.js&quot; ...","url":"fr\/guide\/plugins.html"},{"title":"Bienvenue sur LiteDocs","text":" Bienvenue sur LiteDocs LiteDocs est un g√©n√©rateur de site statique moderne et l√©ger √©crit en PHP. Il est con√ßu pour √™tre rapide, extensible et facile √† utiliser. Pourquoi LiteDocs ? Nous avons cr√©√© LiteDocs car nous avions besoin d'un outil : Simple : Aucune configuration complexe requise. Rapide : √âcrit en PHP 8.4+ pour la performance. Extensible : Syst√®me de plugins valide utilisant Symfony EventDispatcher. Exemple Rapide Voici comment initialiser le kernel en PHP : use LiteDocs\\Core\\Kernel; $kernel = new Kernel(__DIR__); $kernel-&gt;boot(); $kernel-&gt;build(); &lt;div data-search-ignore style=&quot;background: #e0f7fa; color: #006064; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; margin-top: 20px;&quot;&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Astuce :&lt;\/strong&gt; Ce bloc utilise l'attribut &lt;code&gt;data-search-ignore&lt;\/code&gt;. Il sera visible pour l'utilisateur mais ignor√© par le moteur de recherche. &lt;\/div&gt; ...","url":"fr\/index.html"}];